# Orchestrator & task board

PipeWatch is built **task-by-task** from GitHub Issues on the **PipeWatch Roadmap** project (org `mdg-labs`, project **#5**). Sub-agents implement tasks; a verifier checks them.

## Use the orchestrator skill when

- The user asks to "orchestrate", "delegate", "run the roadmap", "implement phase X", or "execute tasks autonomously"
- Multi-step work spans several tasks or an epic

In that case, follow `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md`. Do not improvise.

## Use GitHub issues directly when

- You're implementing a single task and the user already pointed at an issue (e.g. `#12`)
- You're checking dependencies or what's next

Load the issue via MCP `issue_read` or `gh`; read acceptance criteria from the issue body and PRD `§` refs cited there.

## Task lifecycle

| Board Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Backlog | Unrefined / deferred |
| Ready | Fully specified — orchestrator picks from here |
| In Progress | Execution agent working |
| In Review | Execution done — awaiting verifier |
| Done | Verifier PASS — merged to `staging`, issue may still be open |
| Closed | Auto when commit with `fixes #N` lands on `main` |

**Blocking dependencies:** A task blocked by `#N` is **unblocked** when `#N`'s board Status is **Done** or **Closed** — not when the GitHub issue state is `closed` (issues stay open until release to `main`).

## GitHub board status (when orchestrating)

PipeWatch project on GitHub (`mdg-labs/pipewatch`, project **#5**). Commit subjects use issue number: `[#12]`.

- **Any orchestrator target** (single leaf or epic) → present batch plan, then start immediately unless user said `plan only` / `wait`
- **Execution agents** → set project Status **In Progress** on leaf issue(s) and parent when dispatching a child (first action, before code); set **In Review** before verifier handoff
- **Verification agents** → set **Done** after all layers PASS (launch **not** `readonly`); FAIL → **Ready** + comment
- **Orchestrator** → after every verifier PASS, re-query board Status and set **Done** if still **In Review** (source of truth)
- Execution prompts must **not** set Done — see `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/github-board.md`

## Universal acceptance criteria (every task)

Even when not listed in an issue, the verifier applies:

- File / directory naming (`04-naming.mdc`)
- Conventional commits with `[#N]` (`01-git-workflow.mdc`, `07-issue-commit-linking.mdc`)
- TypeScript strict, no `any`, no `console.log` (when TypeScript is in scope)
- Security defaults — JWT/refresh/API-key rules, webhook HMAC, workspace scoping (`03-security-baseline.mdc`)
- Edition flags via `packages/config/edition.ts` — no scattered edition checks (`00-project.mdc`)
- Vendor-neutral schema names in DB/API (`04-naming.mdc`)
- Drizzle schema + migration workflow (`15-db-migrations-schema.mdc`)

## Explicit non-goals (MVP out of scope — PRD §2)

If a request targets any item below, **flag it** and ask whether to defer:

- Webhook Gateway / relay for private CE instances
- Alerts & notification channels (Slack, email)
- Re-running workflows from PipeWatch
- SSO
- Raw log storage / ingestion
- GitHub Enterprise Server
- Additional CI platforms (GitLab, CircleCI, etc.)
- AI-powered failure resolution
